The paper deals with the stable marriage problem, which is a classic problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The concept of popular matchings is well-studied in the literature of computational complexity (cs.CC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a bi-criteria algorithm, which involves optimization techniques and linear programming, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
